      "markdown": "## SOLUTIONS OF NONHOMOGENEOUS SSYSTEMS \n\nWhen a nonhomogeneous S  linear system has many solutions, the general s solution can n be written in parametric vector form as one vector plus an arbitrary  linear combination of vectors that satisfy the corresponding ghomogeneous system.\n\n\n\nExample 3 : Describe all solutions of $A\\mathbf{x}=\\mathbf{b}$ where \n\n$$A={\\left[\\begin{aligned}{3\\quad5\\quad-4}\\\\ {-3\\quad-2\\quad4}\\\\ {6\\quad1\\quad-8}\\end{aligned}\\right]}{\\mathrm{~a n d~}}{\\mathsf{b}}={\\left[\\begin{aligned}{7}\\\\ {-1}\\\\ {-4}\\end{aligned}\\right]}.$$",
